                  <ce:bold>Tom Welton</ce:bold> is Professor of Sustainable Chemistry at Imperial College London. After his undergraduate studies at the University of Sussex he completed a PhD in the <ce:italic>Chemistry and Spectroscopy of Ionic Liquids</ce:italic>. It was his work on the use of ionic liquids as solvents for synthesis that brought him into contact with the emerging field of Green Chemistry in the 1990s. Since then he has developed ionic liquids for the processing of biomass derived polymers.</ce:simple-para>
